Here are some genuinely high-leverage AI use cases that don’t get enough attention:
Scientific Compression
AI reading every paper in a field simultaneously and surfacing cross-domain connections humans miss — not just summarizing, but identifying when a solution in mycology solves a problem in materials science.
Personalized Socratic Tutoring at Scale
Not “explain this topic” — but a system that models your specific misconceptions and engineers the exact question that makes you discover the correct mental model yourself. One-on-one Socratic method for every student on earth.
Regulatory Arbitrage Mapping
Real-time mapping of where a business idea is legal, where it’s in a gray zone, and where it’s blocked — across 190+ jurisdictions simultaneously. Massive for founders and global operators.
Premortem Simulation
Feed in a business plan, military operation, or policy proposal — AI plays every adversarial actor, stress-tests every assumption, and returns a prioritized failure map before you commit resources.
Rare Disease Diagnosis
Most rare diseases take 4–7 years to diagnose because no single doctor has seen enough cases. AI trained across the full corpus of case reports can pattern-match against thousands of conditions simultaneously.
Behavioral Economics in Policy Design
Modeling how populations actually respond to incentives (not how economists assume they do) before deploying social policy. Could prevent enormous waste.
Legal Threat Horizon Scanning
For companies: continuous monitoring of case law, regulatory shifts, and litigation patterns to flag emerging legal risks 12–24 months before they become a crisis.
Oral History Preservation
Recording and structuring the knowledge of elderly experts, elders, and craftspeople — people carrying irreplaceable knowledge — before it’s permanently lost. The AI’s job is knowledge extraction, not generation.
Infrastructure Failure Prediction
Correlating sensor data, weather patterns, maintenance history, and material degradation models to predict bridge, grid, or pipeline failures before they happen.
Negotiation Preparation
Given a counterparty’s public statements, past deals, organizational pressures, and known priorities — AI builds a real-time model of their BATNA and likely concession points before you walk into the room.
Drug Repurposing
Finding existing FDA-approved drugs that work on new targets — compressing a decade of discovery into months by modeling molecular interactions at scale.
Conflict De-escalation Modeling
Simulating how diplomatic communications land with a foreign government — accounting for cultural framing, political pressure on their side, and historical context — before a message is sent.
The real pattern across all of these: AI as a compression engine for expertise that currently doesn’t scale — whether that’s a great doctor, a great lawyer, a great strategist, or a great teacher.​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​